rComments: Math isn't my best subject but she's such a great prof she makes mandatory courses bearable. She is accessible in person and online and she is also really good at further simplifying concepts. There are no surprises on her tests and exam just practice the ones from the years before and you should be good! Take this prof and you won't regret it!
I LOVE HER!!! She is sooo sweet, trust me I suck at math, but I'm surprised I passed with B+! This was hands down my favourite class, love her and the class!!

She tries her best to simplify material and gives you the highest mark possible based on the midterms and exam. She answers emails quickly and is always more than happy to answer questions and does them really well. She's good at what she does and it's not so bad! If you're good at math this should be a really easy course for you and not stressful.

She is the best math professor I've ever had. She truly cares about her students and ensures that she is fair in her exams and midterms. Honestly the best teacher I've had this year, I am so glad I chose her class.

Overall she's a great professor that provides a ton of feedback/practice questions. Only thing I found is that the lectures can be really boring (maybe it's just the fact that it's Linear Algebra). You don't neeeeed to go to class because she posts the notes online and provides a ton of old midterms to study off of. Great prof.

She is very nice and really cares about the students. She posts online feedback reports that we can fill out for her so she knows where we need help, or what she can improve on. Class isn't easy, but she tries her best to make it easy for us:)

Super bonne professeur! Elles est jeunes et comprend vraiment l'importance d'avoir de bonne notes donc elle est toujours disponible pour aider et ses évaluations son clair et simple. Je reprendrais n'importe quel cours avec elle comme professeur!
